RAG: RAG is a system that uses a specific type of database to look up additional information that it can feed into an LLM prompt. The database/datatype is uses is vector encodings, and the idea is that 'close' vectors represent similar ideas/meaning in the text. RAG is used to help specialize agents with specific tasks, overcome the knowledge-cutoff, and reduce hallucinations because of how it provides additional information.
Slippers: Slippers are a shoe type that is meant to be worn indoors and without socks, to keep your feet warm. I've always found it hard to get good slippers. It's hard to get ones that fit the right way, and don't slip off, without being too tight. I feel like all the slippers I have always make my feet too warm, and then they sweat a lot which is uncomfortable.
Cats: Cats are a type of feline mammal that is generally considered a house pet. Cats are considered aloof, and mostly just do their own thing. I think cats are awesome. I would like a cat. If you get the right sort of cat, I'm sure it would be cuddly like a dog.

Dark Chocolate: Dark chocolate is a general category for a cacao ratio in chocolate. It represents the set of high cacao ratio. I think it's really tasty, as long as it's not bitter.
